## Required tool-call chain
The class-interaction pathway is what makes this example valuable — the model cannot rely on a direct hit in `interactions`, it must recognise the class match from `check_warnings` output.

1. `normalize_drug` — called once for "{{ drug_a }}" and once for "{{ drug_b }}".
2. `check_warnings` — called with both resolved drugs. The KB ground truth will surface a CLASS-level interaction (severity {{ severity }}). The model must NOT downgrade this because no direct pair row exists.
3. Final model response — must cite the class mechanism ("{{ mechanism }}" or equivalent plain-language paraphrase) and flag the interaction at severity {{ severity }}. Must include an `AegisResponse` JSON with:
   - flags: [{"severity": {{ severity }}, "type": "drug_interaction", "description": "...", "citation": "FDA prescribing info — {{ class_name_a }} / {{ class_name_b }} class label"}]
   - EVERY flag MUST carry an inline `citation` field naming a real source (FDA / NLM / CPIC / USPSTF / ACIP / AGS Beers / NIH ODS). No flag without a citation.
   - citations: a top-level citations array mirroring the sources referenced in flags
   - defer_to_professional: true (class-level severity {{ severity }} warrants clinical review)

