## Output format
Return a JSON object with a single key "conversation" whose value is a list of turns.
Each turn has "role" (system | user | model) and "content".
Tool calls: <|tool_call>{"name": "...", "arguments": {...}}<tool_call|>
Tool results: <|tool_result>{"name": "...", "result": {...}}<tool_result|>

The user turn should be natural — someone mentioning they take {{ drug_a }} for an existing condition and asking whether {{ drug_b }} is safe to add. Do NOT name the drug classes in the user turn — a real user wouldn't know them. The class reasoning emerges in the model response.

Be medically accurate. Use the KB description and mechanism above as the factual ground truth.
